    <body>
      <head>Richard Saphir</head>
      <div>
        <p>Son of <ref cRef="saphir_josef">Josef Saphir</ref> and his wife <ref
            cRef="saphir_mathilde">Mathilde</ref>. He studied jurisprudence at the University of
          Vienna, and at the same time violin at the Vienna Conservatory (= Akademie f&#xFC;r Musik
          und darstellende Kunst). Having attained his doctorate in law, he opened his own legal
          chancellery in Vienna. As a soldier, he was severely wounded in World War I, was taken
          prisoner and remained in captivity until early 1918.</p>
      </div>
